<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.6363/1262: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-27T19:00:00-04:00">January 27, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>219. Your 235, January 26 and your 195, January 21.<note n="26" xml:id="d320fn1">Neither printed</note> You are authorized to
                                notify Spaniards that February 21 and 22 loadings have been
                                suspended.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>